This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it describes a corpus annotation scheme for evaluating parsers in natural language processing. It may also be relevant to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it discusses the accuracy of a parser, and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it relates to natural language understanding. Additionally, it could be relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as parsers are often used in search engines, and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) as neural networks are commonly used in natural language processing.
